  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this prospective non-interventional neuropsychological one visit study involving
      functional MRI (fMRI) is to ascertain emotional processing in patients with Multiple
      Sclerosis (MS) or Clinically Isolated Syndrome (CIS) compared to healthy control subjects.

      In different experiments, the modulation of cognitive and motor responses by visual emotional
      information and the ability to discriminate visual emotional stimuli will be tested using
      experimental behavioral paradigms. Furthermore, functional connectivity and - using fMRI -
      activations of brain regions known to be involved with emotional processing will be
      evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
